@Dr. Velious The reason I prefer VLR is mostly the accessibility of the timeline and the jumps. In 999 it was pretty brutal to have to replay the beginning so many times, and really prevented you from experimenting properly - or at least from doing so enjoyably.

I can say that personally I couldn't get any of the interesting endings without a walkthrough of some sort. The game doesn't give you enough feedback for whether or not you're on the right track.

From a story perspective, I can see where you're coming from, and the 999 story did feel a lot more personal and straightforward than VLR. I hear they made a version of 999 for phones that has VLR's timeline system, but also removes the escape-the-room segments so I don't know if it's worth it :P
